Christ Centered
Devotion for 1/19 /2007
Let's Live A Life Of Praise Unto
the Lord
Psa 9:2  I will be glad
and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most
High.

Quote
God
makes a promise; faith believes it, hope anticipates it, patience quietly
awaits it.

Today's Verses - KJV
John
10:7-11  Then said Jesus unto them again, Verily, verily, I say unto
you, I am the door of the sheep. All that ever came before me are thieves
and robbers: but the sheep did not hear them. I am the door: by me if any
man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find
pasture. The thief cometh not, but for to steal, and to kill, and to
destroy: I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it
more abundantly. I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life
for the
sheep.

My Comments
There is only one door into the kingdom of God;
Jesus Christ. Those who are trying to get in another way are thieves and
robbers and will not get there. Those who do not believe in Christ are
dead in their sins. The one and only way to life is by Jesus Christ. Some
call this legalistic and narrow minded. This is what caused all the early
disciples to be ridiculed and some were put to death. The gospel is an
offense to some but it is the only way to be eternally saved. That is why
we keep telling it like it is, even though some hate us. We love the Lord
and minister to all who will let us, even if they hate us! We have met the
one who gave His life for us; so we give our all to Him and serve Him with
gladness, because He is The Way, The Truth and The Life. He who gave His
life for us will keep and protect us, if we will allow Him to. Is He your
Shepherd? Meditate on it!

Prayer
Father God, thank You for the gift of life that
is in Jesus Christ. Grant us the anointing to be more effective ministers
of the gospel. We ask, believe we receive, and give thanks in
the Name of Jesus Christ. Amen.

