Psa 9:2  I will be glad
and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most
High.

Quote
Though Christ a
thousand times in Bethlehem be born, If he's not born in thee thy soul is
still forlorn.  ANGELUS SILESIUS
(1624–1677)

Today's Verses - KJV
John 10:14-18  I am the
good shepherd, and know my sheep, and am known of mine. As the Father
knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the
sheep. And other sheep I have, which are not of this fold: them also I
must bring, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and
one shepherd. Therefore doth my Father love me, because I lay down my
life, that I might take it again. No man taketh it from me, but I lay it
down of myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it
again. This commandment have I received of my
Father.

My Comments
No one took the life of Jesus; He gave His life
for "Whosoever will". He didn't wait for us to believe, He did it so we
could believe! While He died and was buried, He didn't stay in the grave.
He came forth on the third day and is alive forever more. He ever lives to
make intercession for those who believe in Him. The next time you are
sorely tried, remember we have much more going for us than against us.
Praise the Lord! He died, not just for one group or one nation; He died
for all who would believe in Him. Christians are the only group who serve
a living Savior! Others are trusting in one who is dead and in their
grave. Meditate on it!

Prayer
Father God, thank You for the gift of salvation
through Your only begotten Son. Thank You for the gift of the Holy Ghost
who shows us Him. &lt;b style="FONT-WEIGHT: ...
