Christ Centered
Devotion for 1/21 /2007

Let's Live A Life Of Praise Unto
the Lord
Isa
62:9  But they that have gathered it shall eat it and praise the LORD; and they that
have brought it together shall drink it in the courts of my
holiness.

Quote
Eternity will not be long
enough to learn all he is, or to praise him for all he has done, but then,
that matters not; for we shall be always with him, and we desire nothing
more.  FREDERICK WILLIAM FABER (1814–1863)

Today's Verses - KJV
John 10:27-30  My sheep hear my voice, and
I know them, and they follow me: And I give unto them eternal life; and
they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.
My Father, which gave them me, is greater than all; and no man is able to
pluck them out of my Father's hand. I and my Father are
one.

My
Comments
Those who belong to the Lord hear His voice and
another they will not listen to or follow. He is always leading in the
paths of righteousness for His name's sake. Those who are in Christ were
given to Him by the Father. No one is able to take us out of the hand of
Christ. Praise the Lord! No one, not even satan, has the authority or
power to remove us from Christ! The only one who can remove us, is we
ourselves. We are commanded to abide in Christ so we will bear much fruit.
He is our strength, ability, and life. It's not us that live but Christ in
us that lives! That is why it is eternal! Are we abiding and bearing the
fruit that shows we are? Are we allowing Him to live in and through us? If
we are it will be a life of holiness and righteousness in Jesus Christ.
Meditate on it!

Prayer
Father God, show us Jesus clearer than we have
seen Him before. We desire to abide in Him and bear the fruit that we are.
May the things we do and say show Christ is in us. We ask, believe we
receive and give thanks in Your Name, Lord Jesus. Amen.

