Psa 9:14  That I may
show forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in thy
salvation.

Quote
At
death we cross from one territory to another, but we'll have no trouble
with visas. Our representative is already there, preparing for our
arrival. As citizens of heaven, our entrance is incontestable. ERWIN
W. LUTZER (1941– )

Today's Verses - KJV
John
11:11-14  These things said he: and after that he saith unto them,
Our friend Lazarus sleepeth; but I go, that I may awake him out of sleep.
Then said his disciples, Lord, if he sleep, he shall do well. Howbeit
Jesus spake of his death: but they thought that he had spoken of taking of
rest in sleep. Then said Jesus unto them plainly, Lazarus is
dead.

My Comments
Everyone of us who are in Christ were, before
receiving Christ, as dead spiritually as Lazarus was naturally. God
declared all dead so He could have mercy on all who would believe in His
only begotten Son, Jesus Christ. That is grace! We had nothing and had
done nothing to merit forgiveness. Forgiveness is the gift of God. Jesus
Christ will give life to all who repent and believe in Him. Believing in
Christ requires us to find out what He says do and don't do and become
doers of that. Here is what He says about this - Luke 6:46  And why
call ye me, Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say? Here is what
the Holy Spirit said in - 1 John 2:3-4  And hereby we do know that
we know him, if we keep his commandments. He that saith, I know him, and
keepeth not his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in
him. Are you a doer of His Word?
Are you keeping His commandments as proof that you truly know Him? Those
who don't, don't know Him!  Meditate on
it!

Prayer
