Jer
17:14  Heal me, O LORD, and I shall be healed; save me, and I shall
be saved: for thou art my praise .

Quote
The Gospels do not explain
the Resurrection; the Resurrection explains the Gospels. Belief in the
Resurrection is not an appendage to the Christian faith; it is the
Christian faith.  JOHN S. WHALE

Today's Verses - KJV
John 11:41-44  Then they took away the
stone from the place where the dead was laid. And Jesus lifted up his
eyes, and said, Father, I thank thee that thou hast heard me. And I knew
that thou hearest me always: but because of the people which stand by I
said it, that they may believe that thou hast sent me. And when he thus
had spoken, he cried with a loud voice, Lazarus, come forth. And he that
was dead came forth, bound hand and foot with graveclothes: and his face
was bound about with a napkin. Jesus saith unto them, Loose him, and let
him go.

My
Comments
Some seem to believe that
when a person dies that is the end of them. The Bible teaches us plainly,
that is not true. Here is what Jesus said about this in John 5:28-29  Marvel
not at this: for the hour is coming, in the which all that are in the
graves shall hear his voice, And shall come forth; they that have done
good, unto the resurrection of life; and they that have done evil, unto
the resurrection of damnation. There will be
a resurrection for all those who have passed on in death. They will be
bodily cast into hell or be forever with the Lord. We will have a new
body, like the Lord's body. 1 Cor
15:53  For this corruptible must put on incorruption, and this mortal
must put on immortality. I will have a
body that won't need to have an artificial leg to be able to walk. I lost
my left leg in a hunting accident when I was nine years old. I am doing
great for a man that has one leg in the grave! All our aches and pains
will be gone forever. We will have a new body, Praise the Lord. Meditate
on it!

Prayer
Father God, thank You for the resurrection. Give
us Your strength and ability to live so we will be among those in the
resurrection of life, in Christ Jesus. We ask, believe we receive and give
thanks in Your Name, Lord Jesus. Amen.

