Psa 22:22  I will
declare thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.

Quote
1 Cor
12:27  Now ye are the body of Christ, and members in
particular.

Today's Verses - KJV
John 12:3-5  Then took
Mary a pound of ointment of spikenard, very costly, and anointed the feet
of Jesus, and wiped his feet with her hair: and the house was filled with
the odour of the ointment. Then saith one of his disciples, Judas
Iscariot, Simon's son, which should betray him, Why was not this ointment
sold for three hundred pence, and given to the
poor?

My Comments
While we may not be able, as Mary did, to bestow
a blessing on the physical body of Christ; when we minister to a brother
or sister in Christ we are ministering to Christ! What we do, good or bad,
to a member of His body; He takes it very personal. The church, made up of
true believers in Christ, are counted as His body. Sometimes we pick and
choose who we will minister to instead of letting the Lord direct us.
Being a respecter of persons is not becoming to one who loves the Lord.
Are we taking advantage of the opportunities to minister to Christ by
ministering to those we come in contact with? The more we take advantage
of those opportunities, the more opportunities we will have! Meditate on
it!

Prayer
Father God, direct us in all we do. Forgive us
when we don't be a vessel You can minister through. Give us eyes to
see others as You see them. We ask, believe we ...
