Jer
20:13  Sing unto the LORD, praise ye the LORD: for he hath
delivered the soul of the poor from the hand of evildoers.

Quote
1 John 2:15-17  Love
not the world, neither the things that are in the world. If any man love
the world, the love of the Father is not in him.  For all that is in
the world, the lust of the flesh, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride
of life, is not of the Father, but is of the world. And the world passeth
away, and the lust thereof: but he that doeth the will of God abideth for
ever.
If I walk with the world, I can't walk with God.
DWIGHT LYMAN MOODY (1837–1899)

Today's Verses - KJV
John 12:23-25  And Jesus answered them,
saying, The hour is come, that the Son of man should be glorified. Verily,
verily, I say unto you, Except a corn of wheat fall into the ground and
die, it abideth alone: but if it die, it bringeth forth much fruit. He
that loveth his life shall lose it; and he that hateth his life in this
world shall keep it unto life eternal.

My
Comments
One who loves the world and
the things that are happening in it, the lust of the flesh, the lust of
the eyes, and the pride of life is not of the Holy Spirit but is of the
world and will not endure forever. We are to love sinners but not what
they do. Their works are of the world. We are citizens of heaven and this
world is not our home. We are just passing through. Only those who are
doing the will of God will abide forever! Praise the Lord. You may ask,
"What is the will of God"? It is clearly outlined in the Word of God. It
starts and ends with abiding in Christ and bearing the fruit that we are.
Sad, but many who claim to love the Lord are in love with the world and
are trying to have both; a love for the Lord and a love for the world.
Beloved, we cannot have both. We must turn loose of one! The question is,
which one will it be? Here is what the Word of God says - 2 Cor 6:17-18
Wherefore come out from among them, and be ye separate, saith the Lord,
and touch not the unclean thing; and I will receive you, And will be a
Father unto you, and ye shall be my sons and daughters, saith the Lord
Almighty. The sons and daughters of
God have done this. Meditate on it!

Prayer
Father God, thank You for the new birth that
causes us to see the world and the things of the world as You see them.
Give us a heart to love the sinner and minister to him as You direct, but
to not love the deeds they do. We ask, believe we receive and give thanks
in Your Name, Lord Jesus. Amen.

