Quote
John 1:8-9  He was not
that Light, but was sent to bear witness of that Light.  That was the
true Light, which lighteth every
man that cometh into the world.

Today's Verses - KJV
John
12:31-33  Now is the judgment of this world: now shall the prince of
this world be cast out. And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, will draw
all men unto me. This he said, signifying what death he should
die.

My Comments
Jesus was lifted up on the cross, between the
earth and heaven, between man and God. He and He alone is the way to know
The Father, God Almighty, as our Father in heaven. There is none other
name known under heaven by which man must be saved. When we witness we are
not lifting up Christ, we are telling that He was lifted up! Beloved, it is
past tense, the work completed and whosoever will can be saved by
repenting and believing on Him, who was lifted up. That is the good news
of the gospel. Notice it says He lights every man that comes into the
world. He draws them unto Himself. As we witness we are not there by
ourselves. Christ is there drawing unto Himself! Do we know that deep
inside of every man there is a vacant spot that only Jesus Christ can
fill! Before surrendering to Christ I knew something was missing in my
life, I just didn't know what to do about it. I tried everything but
nothing filled the empty place in me. Then I repented and received Jesus
Christ as Savior and Lord. Then I found what I was looking for. I had
peace, abiding peace, in my heart for the first time. Praise the Lord! The
hardest person to reach with the gospel is one who has been given false
hope by trusting in something or someone other than Christ. Is Christ your
life? Meditate on it!

